Rules in Dimensions' End: Transcendence
Tiers in Dimensions' End: Transcendence are made up of crucible quests and a reckoning quest.

All crucible quests must be cleared to in order to take on a tier's reckoning quest.

When attempting a reckoning quest, only characters used to clear the tier's crucible quests will be available for inclusion in your party.
Characters used in clearing a crucible quest to will be subject to engagement restrictions.

Using them to clear another crucible quest in the Dimensions' End will reset the status of the previously cleared quest.

The status of a reckoning quest will be reset in the following situations.
• The status of a crucible quest in the same tier is reset.
• A character used to clear the reckoning quest to is not included in the party that reattempts and subsequently clears to a crucible quest in the same tier for which they had previously been included.
*A message will display to confirm any quests that will have their status reset.
Crucible quests will have missions that require using characters of a particular crystal color.
All quests in Dimensions' End: Transcendence will confer a group boost effect that enhances the entire party's stats when a character who is equipped with any of the following is included in the party:

• BT weapon
• Burst command ability
• BT ability
*Group boost effects do not stack.
